<div class="container-fluid conclusion-section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 col-lg-6">
      <h6>The Final Prototype</h6>
      <p>In a trio of services including Ruby on Rails, Heroku, and Amazon Web Services, I produced a lightweight web application that could store and query large masses of data, and with user-feedback and testing, I could ensure techCorp clients that the forms and queries would be reliable to the end-user.</p>
      <p>In preparation for growth, the database schema and architecture was built to encompass large amounts of users, large amounts of data, and the ability to add and merge additional records and associations with the existing data.</p>
      <p>Finally, additional pages were added to the corpus to build trust with the end-user. I included pages such as <strong>About</strong> and <strong>People</strong>, which told the story of the project and its future potential.</p>
